  "response_text": "# Foods and drinks for a cold\n\n**Best options:**\n- **Warm liquids** – broth, tea, warm lemon water with honey, or soup to soothe your throat and stay hydrated\n- **Vitamin C foods** – citrus fruits, berries, kiwi, bell peppers (may help slightly)\n- **Zinc sources** – chicken, nuts, seeds, legumes (may shorten duration if early)\n- **Soft, easy-to-swallow foods** – oatmeal, yogurt, smoothies, mashed potatoes\n- **Ginger and garlic** – anti-inflammatory properties may help\n\n**Stay hydrated:**\n- Water is most important\n- Avoid excessive caffeine and alcohol, which can dehydrate you\n\n**What to limit:**\n- Very hot/spicy foods if your throat is sore\n- Excessive dairy if it increases congestion (varies by person)\n- Sugary foods that may weaken immunity\n\n**General tip:** Eat what sounds tolerable and what you can keep down. Rest and hydration matter more than specific foods.\n\n**See a doctor if** symptoms worsen or last beyond 10 days.\n\nIs there a particular symptom (sore throat, congestion, etc.) that's bothering you most?",
